\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 In a blender, puree the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/watermelon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 watermelon}} and sugar until smooth. Pour the puree through a fine mesh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/strainer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 strainer}}. Transfer the liquid to a pitcher and add the lime juice, tequila and 4 ounces of the Triple Sec. Stir to combine.\
In a shallow dish, combine the kosher salt with the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chili-powder/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chili powder}}. In a second small plate, add the remaining 1-ounce of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/triple-sec/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Triple Sec}}. Dip the rims of 4 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/margarita/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 margarita}} glasses in the Triple Sec, then coat them in the salt and chili mixture. Divide the margarita between the 4 glasses and garnish each with a lime wedge.\
